clinical workflow that manages benefits, prescription verifications, and pharmaceutical handovers. Multiple distinct user roles participate in this care delivery-to-handover cycle:
1. 🏢 Employee (EMPLOYEE)
The Experience: Focuses on submitting, monitoring, and tracking medical benefits and prescription requests.
Key Permissions:
Initiate clinical-benefit prescription dispensation forms for themselves or covered family members (Spouse, Child, Parent, etc.).
Input exact prescriptions, dosage frequencies, and duration terms (30-day refills, 60-day therapies, etc.).
Mark requests as critical care-urgent or require wet-signature validation.
Track the live pipeline status of their active requests at any time.
2. 🩺 Clinical Medical Reviewer (REVIEWER)
The Experience: Clinical-first portal designed for medical justification audit and funding approval.
Key Permissions:
Accesses the medical triage queue of all submitted Pending Review requests.
Evaluates the medical diagnostic reasoning behind benefit submissions.
Approves requests for insurance/co-pay ledger coverage or rejects them with formal medical explanation logs.
3. 🧪 Pharmacy Administrator (PHARMACY_ADMIN)
The Experience: Logistics-centric station for central dispensations and stock control.
Key Permissions:
Receives clinically approved medication files.
Prepares specific formula quantities and records shelf, bin, and batch serial identifiers.
Dispatches the physical medications, moving the status to dispensed.
4. 📦 Prep Operation Packaging Manager (PREP_MANAGER)
The Experience: Focused on pharmaceutical safety, batch insulation, and regulatory packaging compliance.
Key Permissions:
Monitors and prepares dispensed medication for transit packaging.
Ensures safety-insulated bags are correctly sealed with QR tags and tamper-evident materials.
Certifies package readiness for coordinate retrieval.
5. 🚚 Company Delivery Coordinator (COMPANY_COORDINATOR)
The Experience: Ground transport custody, physical handoff, and final feedback loops.
Key Permissions:
Acknowledge receipt and retrieve bundles from central preparation hubs.
Manages on-premises delivery routing to office spaces.
Performs final key-receipt handovers, logs user signatures, and marks requests as fully completed.
6. ✍️ Data Entry Operator (DATA_ENTRY)
The Experience: Record management and bulk processing.
Key Permissions:
Utilizes bulk data processing systems (such as Excel/CSV templates) to mass-upload records.
Manages historical audits and supports the digital recording of offline prescriptions.
7. 👑 Platform Administrator (PLATFORM_ADMIN)
The Experience: High-level telemetry dashboards, systems infrastructure telemetry, and complete organizational audits.
Key Permissions:
Monitors active network database sync relays.
Views aggregate platform activity graphs (such as current processing pipelines, delivery speed charts, and departmental breakdowns).
Examines complete raw system records and exports CSV files for executive reports.
